<item>
            <title>[LU-5732] hsm: sanity check for sane progress extent value</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5732</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During an HSM archive or restore, the progress is reported by the copytool, in userspace. That value may be bogus. For&lt;br/&gt;
instance, this will crash the MDS in interval_set():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    he.offset = -1;&lt;br/&gt;
    he.length = 10;&lt;br/&gt;
    rc = llapi_hsm_action_progress(hcp, &amp;amp;he, length, 0);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So check that userspace is giving a sane progress extent value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
